  "body": "# Bug\r\n\r\nAs you can see in the screenshot below, there's too much space around uncategorized channels in the Community Overview screen.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/46027/ee34e9d8-44eb-4859-bc97-12a71c8cdc0c\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n### Implementation\r\n\r\nIf my memory serves me right, the proper fix may involve a bit of refactoring to make each optional section of the community overview screen only add margins/paddings when it's actually displayed.\r\n\r\n### Resources\r\n\r\n- Screen file: `src/status_im2/contexts/communities/overview/view.cljs`\r\n- Comment from design review https://www.figma.com/file/Tf5nfkYvpbnNCo4rKLK7lS?node-id=3271:192285&mode=design#489874667\r\n- Figma screen Communities for Mobile - https://www.figma.com/file/h9wo4GipgZURbqqr1vShFN/Communities-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=10280-421885&mode=design&t=HnpPfFcU2nPg8xZx-0",
